data.ground_truth:
The specific grounds for removing a Chairperson or Member from the Committee due to sexual harassment in the workplace can be based on any one, all or none of the following reasons:
(a) pending against him; 
(b) found guilty in any disciplinary proceedings; 
(c) abuse of position; 

Based on the given context and title 'The Sexual Harassment of Women at Workplace', it is most likely that the Chairperson or Member being considered for removal has been accused or proven to have engaged in sexual harassment.

